tion process.\"", "\"IMPORTANCE AND IMPLEMENTATION OF ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTING AT LITTLE CHEMICAL CO\":\"The Little Chemical Co (LCC) faced significant fines and loss of customers due to excessive chemical emissions, prompting a need for better environmental management. The company\u2019s management has recognized the importance of environmental management accounting (EMA) to address and manage environmental costs and impacts effectively. EMA provides both physical and monetary information, utilizing techniques like activity-based costing (ABC) to improve environmental performance and decision-making.\"", "\"PROFIT ANALYSIS AND COST CALCULATION FOR PRODUCT D\":\"Scovet Co has identified a market for a new product D and provided estimated sales revenue, contribution percentage, fixed costs, and capital investment. The case involves calculating the total profit over the product's life and the cost per unit, including absorption of all product-specific costs.\"", "\"ANALYSIS OF LIFECYCLE COSTS AND STRATEGIC DECISIONS FOR A NEW FITNESS MONITOR\":\"Fit Co is considering the development of a new fitness monitor with a commercial life of two years. The case includes cost estimates for research, design, marketing, and manufacturing, and involves strategic decisions based on lifecycle costs.\"", "\"PRODUCT DESIGN COSTS\":\"Product design costs are the expenses incurred during the design phase of a new product.\"", "\"VARIABLE LABOUR PRODUCTION COSTS\":\"Variable labour production costs are the expenses related to the labour required to produce each unit of a product.\"", "\"OTHER VARIABLE PRODUCTION COSTS\":\"Other variable production costs are the expenses related to the production of each unit of a product, excluding labour.\"", "\"FIXED PRODUCTION COSTS\":\"Fixed production costs are the expenses that do not vary with the level of production.\"", "\"DISTRIBUTION COSTS\":\"Distribution costs are the expenses related to distributing the product to customers.\"", "\"SELLING COSTS\":\"Selling costs are the expenses related to selling the product.\"", "\"ADMINISTRATION COSTS\":\"Administration costs\" are the expenses related to the general administration and operation of the business. These costs include salaries of administrative staff, office supplies, and rent. Additionally, administration costs will increase by $37,500 every quarter, starting from Q2, due to the employment of a change manager with an annual salary of $150,000. A 3% increase in administration costs has already been adjusted in the figures provided.", "\"LIFE CYCLE COST PER UNIT\":\"Life cycle cost per unit = Total costs / Number of units produced over the life cycle\"", "\"LEARNING EFFECT ON PRODUCTION PROCESS\":\"The learning effect on the production process refers to the reduction in labour time per unit as workers become more efficient with experience.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}